Create the following heading in the lab readme.md file below Data Representation:
Numeric Conversions 
 Explain the difference between decimal, binary and hexadecimal numbers 
  Decimal works in a base base system, binary works in a base two system and hexadecimal works in a base 16 system. All of which rep numbers in a different way.

Convert the decimal number 211 to binary showing your work (be sure to include your name in your screenshot or scanned file)
and save to a file named DecimalConversion and upload to your lab folder. 
 

Convert the binary representation: 10110101 to decimal and save your work to a file named BinaryConversion and upload to the lab folder. 
 

Create the following heading in the lab readme.md file under Data Representation: 
Hexadecimal Color Representation 
 Explain the representation: #ab00ff using the site: https://www.colorhexa.com 
This number is the reprisentation of the code assigned to a specific color (in this case purple).

When considering accessibility in web sites would this color be problematic? Explain what should be considered.
Unless users have a specific kind of eye condition and are offered a method to change the colors used on the site to ones that suit them better, it may 
be wise to avoid using it. It could cause eyestrain or other eye related conditions to flare up. 
